{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"usefulItems":"baking tray and paper, wooden skewer, piping bag (10 mm nozzle), oven","id":"r66930","imageLink":"https:\/\/3.bp.blogspot.com\/-wgJh9LMhJ7o\/XZaqONqyUrI\/AAAAAAAAhaY\/w5Ylt5ypgAM4ROd6R2u1XIlOG5BjIpENwCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_RxPwhyxyqWUpEnfT.png","title":"Choux pastry","publishedAt":"2014-09-05T00:00:00Z","ingredients":[{"content":"150 g water"},{"content":"80 g butter, cut into pieces"},{"content":"1 pinch salt"},{"content":"2 tsp sugar"},{"content":"120 g plain flour"},{"content":"3 eggs"}],"nutrition":{"protein":"2 g","fat":"5 g","uom":"per 1 piece","carbohydrates":"6 g","calories":"300 kJ \/ 72 kcal"},"preparations":[{"content":"Place water, butter, salt and sugar into mixing bowl and cook <b>2 min 30 sec - 5 min\/100°C\/speed 1<b>."},{"content":"Add flour and mix <b>20 sec\/speed 4<b>. Remove mixing bowl and set aside to cool for 10 minutes."},{"content":"Preheat oven to 200°C. Line a baking tray with baking paper and set aside."},{"content":"Place mixing bowl back into position and mix <b>speed 5<b>, adding eggs one at a time through hole in mixing bowl lid onto rotating blades. After adding the last egg, mix a further <b>30 sec\/speed 5<b>."},{"content":"Place pastry mixture into a piping bag and pipe balls (choux) or sticks (éclairs) onto prepared baking tray, leaving 5 cm space between each. Bake for 20 - 25 minutes (200°C) or until golden brown. Turn off oven, remove baking tray and pierce each ball with a wooden skewer to release steam. Return tray to oven and open oven door leaving it ajar for 10 minutes to allow pastry to dry. Remove tray from oven and allow choux pastries to cool completely before filling as desired or serving."}],"hintsAndTricks":["The cooking time required to melt butter in step 1 will depend on the temperature of the butter.","Using a wet finger, smooth down any bumps on the top of choux pastries before baking.","If you don't have a piping bag, cut the corner off a sturdy freezer bag and use to pipe choux pastries onto baking tray.","Choux pastries can be filled with whipped cream or pastry cream and served with fresh fruit, dusted with sugar.","Fill choux pastries with cream cheese and fresh herbs for a savoury option.","Adjust the size and shape of the choux pastries to suit your taste and requirements."],"basicInfo":["medium","20m","2h","18 pieces"]}